<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4536196>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 6. — Hemicosciniopsis incrustans Vigneaux,1949,figured syntype C.B.97-1, Aquitanian,early Miocene,Pessac,Lorient,Gironde,Aquitaine,France.A, general view of the colony; B, group of ovicellate and non-ovicellate zooids; C, close-up of an autozooid and ovicellate zooid showing dimorphic orifices; D, close-up of an autozooid orifice with suboral avicularium; E, close-up of the ovicell and orifice of a maternal zooid; F, close-up of a suboral avicularium showing complete crossbar. Scale bars: A, 500 μm; B, C, 200 μm; D, F, 50 μm; E, 100 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4536196/files/figure.png" .

